  "suspicious-pile-of-sand": {
    "category": "loot-containers",
    "name": "Suspicious Pile of Sand",
    "description": "The Suspicious Pile of Sand is a Loot Container that can only be found at Shipwrecks. Unlike other containers, the pile only has one rarity: Normal.\nIt is suspected that the pile does have a rarity value, but this information is hidden from the players view unlike other containers that state their rarity in the name and by visual color differences. As such, it can only be speculated at if the container contains different drop tables or not.\nThe pile is similar to locked Boxes in that it requires a Key to open, that being a Rusty Shovel, to unearth the pile and get to whatever buried treasure it contains. Unlike locked boxes, the pile is a static object and can not be picked up.\nThe contents within a pile is extremely varied and comes in distinct sets. Data is still being collected on what exactly can be found but notable drops include: Armored Jacket, AV1 Rocket Launcher and Rockets, Triplet Shotgun, and KF866/9R \"Mehrzel\" Repeater.\nLoot Container",
    "sourceUrl": "https://sandgame.wiki/index.php/Suspicious_Pile_of_Sand"
  },
